rsRateLimitMIB.name: rsRateLimitMIB

revisions.description: Second revision. Added more types and tables for Layer 2 rate limiting features and deprecated some invalid values.

rsRateLimitMIB.contactinfo: Riverstone Networks, Inc 5200 Great America Parkway Santa Clara CA USA 95054 PHONE:+1 408.878.6500 EMAIL: nms-eng@riverstonenet.com WEB: http://www.riverstonenet.com
rsRateLimitMIB.description: This mib module defines the Riverstone Networks enterpise MIB for rate limit module. http://www.riverstonenet.com/products. Copyright (C) Riverstone Networks, Inc 2000

RsRateLimit.name: RsRateLimit
RsRateLimit.description: Rate limit on the selected traffic flow is specified using this data type. For RS Platform, this value can be set from 3000..1000000000 bits per second on all line cards.

RsBurst.name: RsBurst
RsBurst.description: Burst traffic rate on the selected traffic flow is specified using this data type. For RS platform, the valid range is 10,000..1000000000 bits per second. This is used for dual token bucket meter or Burst Safe(TM) meter

RsAdminStatus.name: RsAdminStatus
RsAdminStatus.description: Specifies the administrative status enabled or disabled

RsDistAmong.name: RsDistAmong
RsDistAmong.description: Distribute the unused 'bandwidth' among n number of flows, keeping a minimum specified bandwidth For example if the Software based AggregateRate is 10,000,000 MinBandwidth is 500,000 for each flow and Number of flows is 'n =15' leftOverBandwidth = AggregateRate -(n * MinBandwidth) 'leftOverBandwidth' is distributed among RsDistAmong number of flows. RsDistAmong is 5 leftOverBandwidth = 10,000,000 - (15 * 500,000) = 2,500,000 5 flows among 15 will get an extra 2,500,000/5 = 500000 bps
RsDistAmong.reference: Refer Riverstone Networks white paper entitled 'An Overview on Rate Limiting' http://www.riverstonenet.com/technology/rate.shtml

RsMeterType.name: RsMeterType
RsMeterType.description: The type of meter service. The value perFlow(1) indicates that this entry specifies a per L3 flow rate limit. softwareFlowAggregate(2) indicates that this entry specifies a software based rate limit aggregate. This is deprecated. hardwareFlowAggregate(3) indicates that this entry specifies a hardware based flow aggregation rate limit perPort(4) indicates that this entry specifies a port-level rate limit service. burstsafe(5) indicates that this entry specifies a dual bucket rate limit. l2(6) indicates that this entry specifies a layer 2 rate limit service.
RsMeterType.reference: Refer Riverstone Networks white paper entitled 'An Overview on Rate Limiting' http://www.riverstonenet.com/technology/rate.shtml

RsMeterInterval.name: RsMeterInterval
RsMeterInterval.description: RS rate limiting is based on credit bucket scheme. A bucket is filled with certain number of credits, and credits are deducted over a given time period. When the time period is expired, the bucket is filled again with the same number of credits. This TC can be used to select time period. This feature does not allow user to specify the period in 'seconds' but a set of numbers from 0 to 10 only.
RsMeterInterval.reference: Refer Riverstone Networks white paper entitled 'An Overview on Rate Limiting' http://www.riverstonenet.com/technology/rate.shtml

RsLabel.name: RsLabel
RsLabel.description: ASCII character which are Letters,Digits and Under Scores Strings beginning with Digits and Underscores are not allowed

RsTOS.name: RsTOS
RsTOS.description: In IPv4 its the TOS byte of IP packet header. Unsigned integer value which can be mapped to TOS or DSCP depending on the associated rate limit action type

RsIfDirection.name: RsIfDirection
RsIfDirection.description: Specifies a direction of data travel on interface. 'inbound' traffic is operated on during reception from the interface, while 'outbound' traffic is operated on prior to transmission on the interface. 'both' traffic is operated during both reception and prior to transmission on the interface.

RsAction.name: RsAction
RsAction.description: Different actions allowed on the RS switch router Can be associated with rsTBMeterTable, or rsPortRLTable for rate limit purposes Note: not all the actions may be applicable to all the modules

rsRateLimitNotifications.name: rsRateLimitNotifications
rsRateLimitNotifications.description: Group for Rate Limit related Notifications

rsTBMeter.reference: Refer Riverstone Networks white paper 'An Overview of RateLimiting' for more details

rsTBMeterApply.name: rsTBMeterApply
rsTBMeterApply.description: Meter Apply table and associated objects
rsTBMeterApply.reference: Refer Riverstone Networks white paper 'An Overview of RateLimiting' for more details

rsTBMeterApplyMonitor.name: rsTBMeterApplyMonitor
rsTBMeterApplyMonitor.description: Group of token bucket rate limit monitor objects

rsPortRateLimit.name: rsPortRateLimit
rsPortRateLimit.description: Input and Output Port based rate limit tables
rsPortRateLimit.reference: Refer Riverstone Networks white paper 'An Overview of RateLimiting' for more details

rsPortRLMonitor.name: rsPortRLMonitor
rsPortRLMonitor.description: Group of port based rate limit monitor objects

rsL2RLMonitor.name: rsL2RLMonitor
rsL2RLMonitor.description: Group of l2 based rate limit monitor objects

rsRateLimitModes.name: rsRateLimitModes
rsRateLimitModes.description: Group of rate limit mode configuration on RS platform

rsRateLimitGroups.name: rsRateLimitGroups
rsRateLimitGroups.description: All different kinds of groupings used in RS rate limiting

rsTBMeterLastChanged.name: rsTBMeterLastChanged
rsTBMeterLastChanged.description: The value of sysUpTime when last SET operation succeeds on this table.

rsTBMeterCount.name: rsTBMeterCount
rsTBMeterCount.description: Total number of entries in the table

rsTBMeterErrorMessage.name: rsTBMeterErrorMessage
rsTBMeterErrorMessage.description: Description of the error caused from the last SET operation that failed on this table

rsTBMeterEntry.name: rsTBMeterEntry
rsTBMeterEntry.description: A record containing a token bucket service parameters. A new row can be created by setting the appropriate value in the table entry with RowStatus to CreateAndGo. The columns in this table are modifiable when the state of entry RowStatus is equal to 'NotInService' or 'NotReady'

rsTBMeterId.name: rsTBMeterId
rsTBMeterId.description: The administratively assigned name to this Meter entry. This name must be unique across the rate-limit module including port based rate limit module Note: name must be unique across the RS platform ratelimit module

rsTBMeterType.name: rsTBMeterType
rsTBMeterType.description: The type of meter service. The value perFlow(1) indicates that this entry specifies a per L3 flow rate limit. For this type the rsTBMeterRate can take a value between 3000 and 1000000000. Agent must ignore the value in the following fields while validating the row: rsTBMeterBurst RsBurst, rsTBMeterBurstFailAction RsAction, rsTBMeterBurstFailActionRewrite RsTOS, -- rsTBMeterMinimumBandwidth RsRateLimit, -- rsTBMeterDistributeAmong RsDistAmong, softwareFlowAggregate(2) value is deprecated. -- softwareFlowAggregate(2) indicates that this -- entry specifies a software based rate limit aggregate. -- Agent must ignore the value in the following fields while -- validating the row: -- -- rsTBMeterBurst RsBurst, -- rsTBMeterBurstFailAction RsAction, -- rsTBMeterBurstFailActionRewrite RsTOS, hardwareFlowAggregate(3) indicates that this entry specifies a hardware based flow aggregation rate limit For this type the rsTBMeterRate can take a value between 0 and 1000000000. Agent must ignore the value in the following fields while validating the row: rsTBMeterBurst RsBurst, rsTBMeterBurstFailAction RsAction, rsTBMeterBurstFailActionRewrite RsTOS, -- rsTBMeterMinimumBandwidth RsRateLimit, -- rsTBMeterDistributeAmong RsDistAmong, perPort(4) indicates that this entry specifies a port-level rate limit service. For this type the rsTBMeterRate can take a value between 3000 and 1000000000 in outbound direction and between 0 and 1000000000 in inbound direction. Agent must ignore the value in the following fields while validating the row: rsTBMeterBurst RsBurst, rsTBMeterBurstFailAction RsAction, rsTBMeterBurstFailActionRewrite RsTOS, -- rsTBMeterMinimumBandwidth RsRateLimit, -- rsTBMeterDistributeAmong RsDistAmong, burstsafe(5) indicates that this entry specifies a dual bucket rate limit. For this type the rsTBMeterRate can take a value between 10000 and 1000000000. Agent must ignore the value in the following fields while validating the row: -- rsTBMeterMinimumBandwidth RsRateLimit, -- rsTBMeterDistributeAmong RsDistAmong, l2(6) indicates that this entry specifies a layer 2 rate limit. For this type the rsTBMeterRate can take a value between 0 and 1000000000. Agent must ignore the value in the following fields while validating the row: rsTBMeterBurst RsBurst, rsTBMeterBurstFailAction RsAction, rsTBMeterBurstFailActionRewrite RsTOS,

rsTBMeterRate.name: rsTBMeterRate
rsTBMeterRate.description: Token Bucket rate in bits per second. Refer to the Description of rsTBMeterType for acceptable values.

rsTBMeterBurst.name: rsTBMeterBurst
rsTBMeterBurst.description: The burst traffic rate (size) supported. This attribute is used only when rsTBMeterType is set to burstsafe(5) For RS platform rate ranges from 10000 to 1000000000.

rsTBMeterInterval.name: rsTBMeterInterval
rsTBMeterInterval.reference: Refer Riverstone Networks white paper 'An Overview of RateLimiting' for more details
rsTBMeterInterval.description: The time interval used with the token bucket.

rsTBMeterFailAction.name: rsTBMeterFailAction
rsTBMeterFailAction.description: The fail action to take when the traffic rate exceeds rsTBMeterRate. If the Action value indicates TOS rewrite or TOS Precedence rewrite, appropriate rewrite value should be in rsTBMeterFailActionRewrite.

rsTBMeterFailActionRewrite.name: rsTBMeterFailActionRewrite
rsTBMeterFailActionRewrite.description: TOS or TOS Precedence rewrite when the traffic exceeds rsTBMeterRate. rsTBMeterFailAction indicates this object value either TOS or TOS Precedence The object is ignored by agent if rsTBMeterFailAction does not indicate rewrite option.

rsTBMeterBurstFailAction.name: rsTBMeterBurstFailAction
rsTBMeterBurstFailAction.description: The fail action to take when the traffic rate exceeds rsTBMeterBurst. If the Action value indicates TOS rewrite or TOS Precedence rewrite, appropriate rewrite value should be in rsTBMeterBurstFailActionRewrite.

rsTBMeterBurstFailActionRewrite.name: rsTBMeterBurstFailActionRewrite
rsTBMeterBurstFailActionRewrite.description: TOS or TOS Precedence rewrite when the traffic exceeds rsTBMeterBurst, rsTBMeterBurstFailAction indicates this object value either TOS or TOS Precedence The object is ignored by agent if rsTBMeterBurstFailAction does not indicate rewrite option.

rsTBMeterMinimumBandwidth.name: rsTBMeterMinimumBandwidth
rsTBMeterMinimumBandwidth.description: The minimum bandwidth to allocate for each flow when rsTBMeterType is 'softwareFlowAggreage' For RS platform rate ranges from 3000 to 1000000000.

rsTBMeterDistributeAmong.name: rsTBMeterDistributeAmong
rsTBMeterDistributeAmong.description: The rate-limit module allocates the minimum specified bandwidth to each matching flow,and the leftover bandwidth of rsTBMeterAccessRate will be distributed among these number of flow.

rsTBMeterStorageType.name: rsTBMeterStorageType
rsTBMeterStorageType.description: Specify if entry should be persistent or not.

rsTBMeterStatus.name: rsTBMeterStatus
rsTBMeterStatus.description: The RowStatus variable controls the activation, deactivation, or deletion of a meter. Writable variable may not be modified when the row is active.

rsTBMeterApplyLastChanged.name: rsTBMeterApplyLastChanged
rsTBMeterApplyLastChanged.description: The value of sysUpTime when last SET operation succeeds on this table

rsTBMeterApplyCount.name: rsTBMeterApplyCount
rsTBMeterApplyCount.description: The current number of entries in rsTBMeterApplyTable

rsTBMeterApplyErrorMessage.name: rsTBMeterApplyErrorMessage
rsTBMeterApplyErrorMessage.description: Description of the error of the last SET operations to fail on this table

rsTBMeterApplyMasterAdminStatus.name: rsTBMeterApplyMasterAdminStatus
rsTBMeterApplyMasterAdminStatus.description: This object enables or disables all the entries in rsTBMeterApplyTable. This behaves like master fuse and do not change individual states of each row. User must check the state of this object before he tries to enable the state of entry.

rsTBMeterApplyTable.name: rsTBMeterApplyTable
rsTBMeterApplyTable.description: This table associates rate limits with interfaces. In particular, a profile from the rsTBMeter table with name rsTBMeterId2 is applied on certain IP interfaces and ports specified by ifIndex with classifier specified by rsTBMeterApplyAclName

rsTBMeterApplyEntry.name: rsTBMeterApplyEntry
rsTBMeterApplyEntry.description: 'ifIndex' is imported from IF-MIB. For RS platform, this value must point to an entry that has ifType of IP interface(126) ethernetCsmacd(6) L4 bridging MUST be enabled on the port before creating the entry. To enable/disable the L4 bridging state on a particular port use VLAN-EXTENSION-MIB module. The columns in this table are modifiable when the state of rsTBMeterApplyStatus equal to NotInService, NotReady.

rsTBMeterApplyAclName.name: rsTBMeterApplyAclName
rsTBMeterApplyAclName.description: Access Control List name or Classifier Name, Must exist on the underlying system before activation.

rsTBMeterId2.name: rsTBMeterId2
rsTBMeterId2.description: The meter id from rsTBMeterEntry.rsTBMeterId. rsTBMeterId must be an active row in rsTBMeterTable.

rsTBMeterApplyOwner.name: rsTBMeterApplyOwner
rsTBMeterApplyOwner.description: The owner of this rate limit apply entry. The exact semantics of this string are subject to the security policy defined by the security administrator. If this entry was created via Command Line Interface, this will be set to 'monitor'

rsTBMeterApplyAdminStatus.name: rsTBMeterApplyAdminStatus
rsTBMeterApplyAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the rate limit entry.

rsTBMeterApplyStorageType.name: rsTBMeterApplyStorageType
rsTBMeterApplyStorageType.description: Specify if entry should be persistent or not.

rsTBMeterApplyStatus.name: rsTBMeterApplyStatus
rsTBMeterApplyStatus.description: Allows to create a new row and modify or destroy an existing row in the manner described in the definition of the RowStatus textual convention

rsPortRLLastChanged.name: rsPortRLLastChanged
rsPortRLLastChanged.description: The value of sysUpTime when last SET operation succeeds on this table

rsPortRLCount.name: rsPortRLCount
rsPortRLCount.description: The current number of entries in rsPortRLTable

rsPortRLErrorMessage.name: rsPortRLErrorMessage
rsPortRLErrorMessage.description: Description of the error caused when the last SET operation failed on this table

rsPortRLMasterAdminStatus.name: rsPortRLMasterAdminStatus
rsPortRLMasterAdminStatus.description: This object enables or disables all the entries in rsPortRLTable. This behaves like master fuse and do not change individual states of each row. User must check the state of this object before he tries to enable the state of an entry in rsPortRLTAble.

rsPortRLTable.name: rsPortRLTable
rsPortRLTable.description: An entry which allows to create port based ratelimit service and to activate it on a physical port

rsPortRLEntry.name: rsPortRLEntry
rsPortRLEntry.description: 'ifIndex' is imported from IF-MIB, which carries an index for physical port. For RS platform, this value must point to an entry that has ifType of ethernetCsmacd(6). The columns in this table are modifiable when the state of rsPortRLStatus equal to NotInService, NotReady.

rsPortRLDirection.name: rsPortRLDirection
rsPortRLDirection.description: Input/Output direction to apply rate limit on a port

rsPortRLMeterId.name: rsPortRLMeterId
rsPortRLMeterId.description: Administratively assigned name to port based rate limit entry Note: name must be unique across the RS platform ratelimit module

rsPortRLOwner.name: rsPortRLOwner
rsPortRLOwner.description: The owner of this entry. The exact semantics of this string are subject to the security policy defined by the security administrator.

rsPortRLRate.name: rsPortRLRate
rsPortRLRate.description: Rate to limit port traffic to. For RS platform rate ranges from 3000 to 1000000000.

rsPortRLFailAction.name: rsPortRLFailAction
rsPortRLFailAction.description: The action to take when the traffic rate exceeds rsPortRLRate. If the Action value indicates TOS rewrite or TOS Precedence rewrite, appropriate rewrite value should be in rsPortRLFailActionRewrite.

rsPortRLFailActionRewrite.name: rsPortRLFailActionRewrite
rsPortRLFailActionRewrite.description: TOS or TOS Precedence rewrite when the traffic exceeds rsPortRLRate. rsPortRLFailAction indicates this object value either TOS or TOS Precedence The object is ignored by agent if rsPortRLFailAction does not indicate rewrite option.

rsPortRLInterval.name: rsPortRLInterval
rsPortRLInterval.reference: Refer Riverstone Networks white paper 'An Overview of RateLimiting' for more details
rsPortRLInterval.description: The time interval used with the token bucket.

rsPortRLAdminStatus.name: rsPortRLAdminStatus
rsPortRLAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the rate limit entry.

rsPortRLStorageType.name: rsPortRLStorageType
rsPortRLStorageType.description: Specify if entry should be persistent or not.

rsPortRLStatus.name: rsPortRLStatus
rsPortRLStatus.description: Allows to create a new row and modify or destroy an existing row in the manner described in the definition of the RowStatus textual convention

rsL2RLApplyLastChanged.name: rsL2RLApplyLastChanged
rsL2RLApplyLastChanged.description: The value of sysUpTime when last SET operation succeeds on this table

rsL2RLApplyCount.name: rsL2RLApplyCount
rsL2RLApplyCount.description: The current number of entries in rsL2RLApplyTable

rsL2RLApplyErrorMessage.name: rsL2RLApplyErrorMessage
rsL2RLApplyErrorMessage.description: Description of the error of the last SET operations to fail on this table

rsL2RLApplyMasterAdminStatus.name: rsL2RLApplyMasterAdminStatus
rsL2RLApplyMasterAdminStatus.description: This object enables or disables all the entries in rsL2RLApplyTable. This behaves like master fuse and do not change individual states of each row. User must check the state of this object before he tries to enable the state of entry.

rsL2RLApplyTable.name: rsL2RLApplyTable
rsL2RLApplyTable.description: This table associates rate limits with port / portgroups / filter / filtergroups. In particular, a profile from the rsTBMeter table with name rsTBMeterId is applied on certain ports specified by ifIndex or the port groups specified with rsL2RLApplyPortGroupName with filter specified by rsL2RLApplyFilterName or the filter groups specified with the rsL2RLApplyFilterName or the classifier mentioned in the entry.

rsL2RLApplyEntry.name: rsL2RLApplyEntry
rsL2RLApplyEntry.description: 'ifIndex' is imported from IF-MIB. For RS platform, this value must point to an entry that has ifType of ethernetCsmacd(6) The columns in this table are modifiable when the state of rsL2RLApplyStatus equal to NotInService, NotReady.

rsL2RLApplyIfIndex.name: rsL2RLApplyIfIndex
rsL2RLApplyIfIndex.description: When the service is applied on a single port, this value should be the ifIndex of the port where the service is applied. If it is applied on a group of ports, this value should be zero. If it is nonZero, the rsL2RLApplyPortGroupName should be a zero length octet string.

rsL2RLApplyPortGroupName.name: rsL2RLApplyPortGroupName
rsL2RLApplyPortGroupName.description: This object identifies one or more rows in the rsRLPortGroupTable, when it of length nonzero. In this case the rsL2RLApplyIfIndex should be zero. If the service is applied on a single port, this object is supposed to be a zero length octet string.

rsL2RLApplyFilterName.name: rsL2RLApplyFilterName
rsL2RLApplyFilterName.description: Filter name or Classifier Name, Must exist on the underlying system before activation. If rsL2RLIsFilterGroup is set to true, then this name specifies the filter group name. The actual filters associated to this entry are specified in rsRLFilterGroupTable. If both filter and port groups are present, this value should be same as the rsL2RLApplyPortGroupName.

rsL2RLIsFilterGroup.name: rsL2RLIsFilterGroup
rsL2RLIsFilterGroup.description: When this value is set to true, then rsL2RLApplyFilterName specifies the group of filters mentioned in the rsRLFilterGroupTable. If set to false, the rsL2RLApplyFilterName specifies the filter name associated with the service.

rsL2RLApplyOnePGrouping.name: rsL2RLApplyOnePGrouping
rsL2RLApplyOnePGrouping.description: This object specifies the 802.1p priority groupings for which this service is to be applied. Currently, 4 different groups can be constructed and those priorities which are not in any groups is put under other category.

rsL2RLApplyOwner.name: rsL2RLApplyOwner
rsL2RLApplyOwner.description: The owner of this rate limit apply entry. The exact semantics of this string are subject to the security policy defined by the security administrator. If this entry was created via Command Line Interface, this will be set to 'monitor'

rsL2RLApplyAdminStatus.name: rsL2RLApplyAdminStatus
rsL2RLApplyAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the rate limit entry.

rsL2RLApplyStorageType.name: rsL2RLApplyStorageType
rsL2RLApplyStorageType.description: Specify if entry should be persistent or not.

rsL2RLApplyStatus.name: rsL2RLApplyStatus
rsL2RLApplyStatus.description: Allows to create a new row and modify or destroy an existing row in the manner described in the definition of the RowStatus textual convention

rsRLModeLastChanged.name: rsRLModeLastChanged
rsRLModeLastChanged.description: The value of sysUpTime when last SET operation succeeds on this table

rsRLModeTable.name: rsRLModeTable
rsRLModeTable.description: Entry of rate limit mode and input port ratelimit state The rows in this table are created dynamically by inserting line cards in their respective slots of the underlying system. When a slot/module is activated resulting entry in this table will have the default operating modes. Essentially the ratelimit mode and input port ratelimit status value. Certain SET operation on this entry might fail if the underlying hardware does not support the mode.

rsRLModeEntry.name: rsRLModeEntry
rsRLModeEntry.description: A record containing ratelimt mode on given module/slot. The columns in this entry are modifiable. This is indexed by entPhysicalIndex whose entPhysicalClass == module(9).

rsRLModeType.name: rsRLModeType
rsRLModeType.description: Type of rate limit modes supported on this slot Value is writable only when rsRLModeCapabilityBits has rlMode(0) set to '1'. The table below relates the ratelimit type supported in each Mode. +---------------------+----------+--------------+ |RsMeterType | flowMode | aggregateMode| +---------------------+----------+--------------+ |perFlow(1) | X | | |softFlowAgg(2) | X | | |hardFlowAgg(3) | | X | |perPort(4) -input | | X | |perPort(4) -output | X | X | +---------------------+----------+--------------+ X indicates supported.

rsRLModeInputPortStatus.name: rsRLModeInputPortStatus
rsRLModeInputPortStatus.description: Input Port RateLimit status on this slot. Value is writable only when rsRLModeCapabilityBits has rlInputPortRateLimit set to '1'.

rsRLModeCapabilityBits.name: rsRLModeCapabilityBits
rsRLModeCapabilityBits.description: Specifies the Module capability. rlMode(0) if set to 1 indicates the Module supports the Flow or Aggregate mode. rlInputPortRateLimit(1) if set to 1 indicates the Module supports input port based rate limiting.

rsRLModeEntryLastChanged.name: rsRLModeEntryLastChanged
rsRLModeEntryLastChanged.description: The value of sysUpTime when last SET operation succeeds on this entry

rsRLPortGroupLastChanged.name: rsRLPortGroupLastChanged
rsRLPortGroupLastChanged.description: The value of sysUpTime when last SET operation succeeds on this table

rsRLPortGroupTable.name: rsRLPortGroupTable
rsRLPortGroupTable.description: This table is to associate one or more ports as a group.

rsRLPortGroupEntry.name: rsRLPortGroupEntry
rsRLPortGroupEntry.description: A record containing group name and ifIndex.

rsRLPortGroupName.name: rsRLPortGroupName
rsRLPortGroupName.description: The administratively assigned name to this PortGroup entry.

rsRLPortGroupStorageType.name: rsRLPortGroupStorageType
rsRLPortGroupStorageType.description: Storage type for this entry. The value of this entry will be the same as the one specified in the row of rsL2RLApplyTable where this group is used. If none of the entries use this group, then the storage type will be volatile.

rsRLPortGroupStatus.name: rsRLPortGroupStatus
rsRLPortGroupStatus.description: Allows to create a new row and modify or destroy an existing row in the manner described in the definition of the RowStatus textual convention

rsRLFilterGroupLastChanged.name: rsRLFilterGroupLastChanged
rsRLFilterGroupLastChanged.description: The value of sysUpTime when last SET operation succeeds on this table

rsRLFilterGroupTable.name: rsRLFilterGroupTable
rsRLFilterGroupTable.description: This table is to associate one or more ports as a group.

rsRLFilterGroupEntry.name: rsRLFilterGroupEntry
rsRLFilterGroupEntry.description: A record containing group name and filter name.

rsRLFilterGroupName.name: rsRLFilterGroupName
rsRLFilterGroupName.description: The administratively assigned name to this FilterGroup entry.

rsRLFilterName.name: rsRLFilterName
rsRLFilterName.description: The name of the filter part of this group.

rsRLFilterGroupStorageType.name: rsRLFilterGroupStorageType
rsRLFilterGroupStorageType.description: Storage type for this entry. The value of this entry will be the same as the one specified in the row of rsL2RLApplyTable where this group is used. If none of the entries use this group, then the storage type will be volatile.

rsRLFilterGroupStatus.name: rsRLFilterGroupStatus
rsRLFilterGroupStatus.description: Allows to create a new row and modify or destroy an existing row in the manner described in the definition of the RowStatus textual convention

rsTBMeterMonitorTable.name: rsTBMeterMonitorTable
rsTBMeterMonitorTable.description: Table which carries exceed count for each token bucket meter applied on Access Control List.

rsTBMeterMonitorEntry.name: rsTBMeterMonitorEntry
rsTBMeterMonitorEntry.description: This is a read only table of exceed count for each token bucket entry applied on Access Contol List.

rsTBMeterExceedByteCount.name: rsTBMeterExceedByteCount
rsTBMeterExceedByteCount.description: Total number of bytes exceeded as a result of traffic rate limiting on a particular rsTBMeterApplyEntry entry. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of rsTBMeterCounterDiscontinuityTime.

rsTBMeterCounterDiscontinuityTime.name: rsTBMeterCounterDiscontinuityTime
rsTBMeterCounterDiscontinuityTime.description: The value of sysUpTime on the most recent occasion at which this counters suffered a discontinuity. If no such discontinuities have occurred since the last re- initialization of the local management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

rsTBMeterExceedPacketCount.name: rsTBMeterExceedPacketCount
rsTBMeterExceedPacketCount.description: Total number of packets exceeded the specified traffic rate limiting on a particular rsTBMeterApplyEntry entry. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of rsTBMeterCounterDiscontinuityTime.

rsTBMeterExceedBurstPacketCount.name: rsTBMeterExceedBurstPacketCount
rsTBMeterExceedBurstPacketCount.description: Total number of packets exceeded the specified burst rate on a particular rsTBMeterApplyEntry entry. This is object is valid only when the rsTBMeterType is burstsafe(5) in the row referred by the rsTBMeterId2 in the rsTBMeterTable. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of rsTBMeterCounterDiscontinuityTime.

rsPortRLMonitorTable.name: rsPortRLMonitorTable
rsPortRLMonitorTable.description: Table which carries exceed count for each token bucket meter applied on the port based ones.

rsPortRLMonitorEntry.name: rsPortRLMonitorEntry
rsPortRLMonitorEntry.description: This is a read only table of exceed count for each token bucket entry applied the port based ones.

rsPortRLExceedByteCount.name: rsPortRLExceedByteCount
rsPortRLExceedByteCount.description: Total number of bytes exceeded as a result of traffic rate limiting on a particular rsPortRLEntry entry. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of rsPortRLCounterDiscontinuityTime.

rsPortRLCounterDiscontinuityTime.name: rsPortRLCounterDiscontinuityTime
rsPortRLCounterDiscontinuityTime.description: The value of sysUpTime on the most recent occasion at which this counters suffered a discontinuity. If no such discontinuities have occurred since the last re- initialization of the local management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

rsPortRLExceedPacketCount.name: rsPortRLExceedPacketCount
rsPortRLExceedPacketCount.description: Total number of packets that exceeded the specified traffic rate limiting on a particular rsPortRLEntry entry. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of rsPortRLCounterDiscontinuityTime.

rsL2RLMonitorTable.name: rsL2RLMonitorTable
rsL2RLMonitorTable.description: Table which carries exceed count for each token bucket meter applied on L2 Filter or Filter Group.

rsL2RLMonitorEntry.name: rsL2RLMonitorEntry
rsL2RLMonitorEntry.description: This is a read only table of exceed count for each token bucket entry applied on L2 Filter or Filter Groups.

rsL2RLExceedByteCount.name: rsL2RLExceedByteCount
rsL2RLExceedByteCount.description: Total number of bytes that exceeded the specified traffic rate limiting on a particular rsL2RLApplyEntry entry. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of rsL2RLCounterDiscontinuityTime.

rsL2RLExceedPacketCount.name: rsL2RLExceedPacketCount
rsL2RLExceedPacketCount.description: Total number of packets that exceeded the specified traffic rate limiting on a particular rsL2RLApplyEntry entry. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system, and at other times as indicated by the value of rsL2RLCounterDiscontinuityTime.

rsL2RLCounterDiscontinuityTime.name: rsL2RLCounterDiscontinuityTime
